			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">How about a stationary ward-like pet, that casts DS as a song (hits the short buff box)? That will alleviate the current problem of DS taking up valuable HoT buff slots on raids or high-end grouping situations.
<br />

<br />
I thought of a couple options for implementation. Make it an AA that adds 25/ 50/100pt ds to all PCs within standard song radius or give it 15/30/50 ds but *stackable* with standard DS and with *other* DS wards. I personally like the second option as it doesn't lower our current DS line's desirability *and* it makes having several mages on the raid quite powerful. AE rampage mobs stand to take quite a beating if the whole raid has 100pts (or more) of DS on them. 
<br />

<br />
Aqui<br />_________________<br />Aquilistor Apotropacus
